modules.description: Provides functions to create, query, and manipulate relations between program elements, including merging, intersecting, and projecting relation graphs. Works with graph structures representing dependencies, control flow, and data flow in binary analysis. Used to track operand dependencies and instruction relationships during static analysis.

Provides operations to manage bidirectional mappings between two sets, including adding, checking, and querying pairs. Works with key-value pairs and computes bijections between sets. Used to analyze and process relationships in symbolic execution or program analysis contexts.
